@page "/components/feedback/signalr-connection-status/accessibility"
@layout MainLayout
@using Sunfish.UIAdapters.Blazor.Components.Showcase

<PageTitle>SignalR Status / Accessibility · Sunfish Kitchen Sink</PageTitle>

<SunfishExamplePanel Title="SignalR Status / Accessibility"
                     Breadcrumb="@_breadcrumb"
                     GitHubUrl="https://github.com/ctwoodwa/Sunfish/blob/main/apps/kitchen-sink/Pages/Components/Feedback/SignalRStatus/Accessibility/Demo.razor"
                     Sources="@GeneratedSources">

    <Narrative>
        <p>
            The <code>SunfishSignalRConnectionStatus</code> trigger is a native
            <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> with <code>aria-haspopup="dialog"</code> and a
            reflected <code>aria-expanded</code> so assistive tech announces it as
            &ldquo;SignalR: all 3 hubs healthy, button, collapsed&rdquo;. The popup is a
            <code>role="dialog"</code> region with a visible header, and each hub is rendered
            through <code>HubConnectionRow</code> which announces a textual health label
            (<em>Healthy / Starting / Recovering / Degraded / Offline</em>) so state is not
            conveyed by colour alone.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Keyboard &mdash; trigger</strong>: <kbd>Tab</kbd> to focus,
                <kbd>Enter</kbd> / <kbd>Space</kbd> to open the popup.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Keyboard &mdash; popup</strong>: <kbd>Tab</kbd> cycles through hub rows
                and the <em>Reconnect</em> button on any offline hub; clicking the scrim or
                pressing <kbd>Esc</kbd> closes the popup.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Accessible name</strong>: the <code>aria-label</code> is generated from
                the aggregate summary (e.g. &ldquo;SignalR: 1 of 3 hubs unhealthy&rdquo;) and
                updates live &mdash; screen readers announce the new label each time the
                registry's <code>Changed</code> event fires.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Textual health labels</strong>: every row carries both a coloured badge
                and a short label (<em>Healthy</em>, <em>Offline</em>, etc.) so the meaning
                survives high-contrast and monochrome rendering.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </Narrative>

    <Example>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1.25rem;">

            <SunfishAlert Severity="AlertSeverity.Info">
                <strong>Backend required.</strong> The live component injects
                <code>ISignalRConnectionRegistry</code>. Kitchen-sink does not register hubs,
                so the reference markup below documents the emitted semantics.
            </SunfishAlert>

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">Keyboard interactions</h3>
                <table style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%; max-width:480px;">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th style="text-align: start; padding:.4rem .6rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--sf-color-border, #ddd);">Key</th>
                            <th style="text-align: start; padding:.4rem .6rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--sf-color-border, #ddd);">Action</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        @foreach (var (key, action) in _keyboard)
                        {
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding:.4rem .6rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--sf-color-border, #eee);">
                                    @((MarkupString)key)
                                </td>
                                <td style="padding:.4rem .6rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--sf-color-border, #eee);">@action</td>
                            </tr>
                        }
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">ARIA attributes (emitted by the component)</h3>
                <dl style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr; gap:.4rem 1rem; margin:0;">
                    <dt><code>aria-label</code></dt>
                    <dd>Live aggregate summary &mdash; e.g. &ldquo;SignalR: 1 of 3 hubs unhealthy&rdquo;.</dd>

                    <dt><code>aria-haspopup="dialog"</code></dt>
                    <dd>Advertises the popup as a dialog.</dd>

                    <dt><code>aria-expanded</code></dt>
                    <dd>Reflects the popup open/closed state.</dd>

                    <dt><code>role="dialog"</code></dt>
                    <dd>Applied to the popup container.</dd>

                    <dt><code>role="listitem"</code></dt>
                    <dd>Applied to every hub row inside the popup.</dd>
                </dl>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 .5rem;">Screen-reader notes</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>The trigger's <code>title</code> and <code>aria-label</code> are identical, so a hover tooltip and a screen-reader announcement stay in sync.</li>
                    <li>Health is always announced in words (<em>Healthy</em>, <em>Recovering</em>, <em>Offline</em>) &mdash; never through colour alone.</li>
                    <li>The popup header text (<code>Title</code>) labels the dialog; set a project-specific value (&ldquo;Real-time feeds&rdquo;, &ldquo;Live data&rdquo;) for clarity.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

        </div>
    </Example>

</SunfishExamplePanel>

@code {
    private static readonly string[] _breadcrumb =
        ["Components", "Feedback", "SignalR Status", "Accessibility"];

    private static readonly (string Key, string Action)[] _keyboard =
    [
        ("<kbd>Tab</kbd>",              "Focus the status trigger"),
        ("<kbd>Enter</kbd> / <kbd>Space</kbd>", "Open or close the popup"),
        ("<kbd>Tab</kbd> (popup open)", "Cycle through hub rows and the Reconnect button"),
        ("<kbd>Esc</kbd>",              "Close the popup and return focus to the trigger"),
        ("<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>Tab</kbd>", "Reverse focus order"),
    ];
}
